        "title": "fix(channels): keep preview streaming from inheriting block defaults",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Telegram or Discord users who configure live preview streaming could still get normal block-message delivery when `agents.defaults.blockStreamingDefault` was enabled.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nTelegram and Discord now resolve block delivery at the channel boundary: explicit channel block-streaming config still wins, live preview modes (`partial`, `progress`, and edit-capable `block`) suppress inherited global block delivery, and `streaming.mode: \"off\"` can still inherit the global default. Slack and WhatsApp were checked and left unchanged: Slack already suppresses block delivery while native/draft preview streaming is active, and WhatsApp does not have the same local `streaming.mode` preview surface.\n\n## User Impact\n\nTelegram and Discord preview streaming now stays on the intended single preview/update path unless block streaming is explicitly enabled for that channel. OpenClaw defaults are unchanged, including Discord's unset `progress` preview mode.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot.helpers.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/doctor.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/message-handler.process.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/native-command-agent-reply.test.ts` passed: 280 tests.\n- `git diff HEAD~1..HEAD --check` passed.\n- Autoreview was attempted but blocked by local reviewer auth/tool availability: Codex returned `token_invalidated`, Copilot executable was not installed, and Claude returned organization access 403.",
